			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Oil doesnt come from dinosaurs.  It comes from the remains of the massive mats (miles thick) of simple organisms that covered the earth millions of years ago.  This same process still occurs, although not on that scale, in oxygen-deficient waters, such as the Black sea.
<br />

<br />
This inorganic theory has been around for some time.  Although theoretically possible, hard evidence has yet to be seen.  A test of this theory was done in the 1980's in the Baltic area, in an area that was definately oil-less.  They drilled and drilled and guess what?  No oil.  I believe several other wells were dug, but I cant recall where.
<br />

<br />
The helium mentioned in the article is probably formed from the gigantic ball of uranium that is at the center of the earth, the one that powers our electromagnetic field and keeps the Earth hot.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
