			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				The lighter elements on earth rise and the heavier ones move toward the center.  Thus we have an atmosphere above water that is above rock (except where rock has pushed up in piles sticking out of the water.
<br />

<br />
If there is Uranium on earth, and there is, most of it would be near the center with the rest of the really heavy elements.
<br />

<br />
I do not know one geologist that has ever contended that seismic testing of the earths core was conclusive of anything.  We have VERY little data and absolutely no clue what the consistancy is like.  Our understanding will definitly be changing as we get more data so Im not ready to dismiss any hypothesis.
<br />

<br />
###
<br />

<br />
Diamonds rise from the earth in columns from deeper in the crust than any organic material could be found.  There is good evidence that there is an inorganic source of carbon from within the earth.  However the area of the midles east, the rockies and the caspian sea have all been strongly linked to organic material.
<br />

<br />
The Shale in Utah for instance holds massive fossil records.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
